  "title": "Sales Administrator / Coordinator (Support)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary: </strong><br /><strong>Salary Range:</strong> $2,700 – $3,000<br /><strong>Working Days:</strong> Monday to Friday<br /><strong>Working Hours:</strong> 8:00am – 5:30pm<br /><strong>Location:</strong> Tuas, Singapore<br /><strong>Benefits: </strong>Phone Allowance, Transport Allowance & Company Transport (Boon Lay)<br /><br /><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>We are looking for a Sales Administrator / Coordinator to support our indoor sales operations and customer retention efforts. This role involves handling customer enquiries, preparing quotations, and providing administrative support to the sales team.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Respond to customer enquiries and emails in a timely and professional manner</p></li><li><p>Prepare, issue, and follow up on quotations and purchase orders</p></li><li><p>Make outbound calls to support customer engagement and retention</p></li><li><p>Maintain and update customer records and databases accurately</p></li><li><p>Support sales administration and coordination activities</p></li><li><p>Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned</p></li></ul><h3>Job Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>O Level / A Level / NITEC / Higher NITEC / Diploma</strong>, or equivalent</p></li><li><p><strong>1–3 years of relevant working experience</strong> in sales support, customer service, or administrative roles is preferred</p></li><li><p>Knowledge or experience in the <strong>chemical-related industry</strong> is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Proficient in <strong>Microsoft Office</strong> (Word, Excel, Outlook)</p></li><li><p>Customer-oriented with a positive and professional attitude</p></li></ul><p>Applicants who possess relevant experience for the above responsibilities are most welcome to apply. If you do not possess the above experience, your application will still be considered on individual merits and you may be contacted for other opportunities.</p><p>Please submit your updated resume in MS Words format by using the <strong>APPLY NOW BUTTON.</strong></p><p>By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by the company relating to this job application.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.mci.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/MCI-Job-Applicant-Data-Protection-Notice.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.mci.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/MCI-Job-Applicant-Data-Protection-Notice.pdf</a></p><p>**We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates would be notified.<br /><br /><strong>Yong Jia Wen</strong></p><p><strong>Registration Number: R25146805</strong></p><p><strong>EA License No: 13C6730 (MCI Consulting Pte Ltd)</strong></p>",
